<headline>Winter Storm Watch issued January 02 at 2:31AM MST until January 04 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Boise</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY AFTERNOON
THROUGH TUESDAY AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...Heavy snow and strong winds. Total snow accumulations of
6 to 10 inches possible, except up to 18 inches over the higher
mountains. Wind gusts to 30 mph in Baker County, Oregon, and in
west-central Idaho, and up to 50 mph in southeast Oregon and
Idaho near the Nevada border will cause blowing and drifting of
snow.
* WHERE...Portions of northeast Oregon and southwest and west
central Idaho.
* WHEN...From Monday afternoon through Tuesday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Travel could become very difficult. Gusty winds
could bring down tree branches and cause blowing and drifting
of snow.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
